CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape High Court has sentenced Cameron Wilson to four life terms and 71 years behind bars. The 21-year-old smiled and clapped while Judge Chantal Fortuin handed down the sentence on Thursday.Wilson was found guilty of several crimes, including murder, rape and attempted murder.READ: Family calls for harsh punishment in Cameron Wilson caseHe was arrested for the murder of 18-year-old Lekita Moore in Valhalla Park in Cape Town last year.Moore s mutilated body was found in an open field after she d been stabbed 98 times.Wilson was also found guilty of murdering four others.One of his victims survived the attack and testified against Wilson.eNCA